To find the sum of \( 211112001_{3} + 1202212200_{3} \), we first must align the two numbers properly and add them together:

\[
\begin{array}{r}
\phantom{0}211112001_{3} \\
+1202212200_{3} \\
\hline
\end{array}
\]

Adding the numbers column by column:

\[
\begin{array}{r}
\phantom{0}211112001_{3} \\
+1202212200_{3} \\
\hline
\phantom{0}3311001201_{3}
\end{array}
\]

Therefore, \(211112001_{3} + 1202212200_{3} = 3311001201_{3}\).